---
import ServiceCityPage from '~/components/pages/ServiceCityPage.astro';
import { services, cities } from '~/data/service-city-config';
---

<ServiceCityPage service={services['generators']} city={cities['hudsonville-mi']}>
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>Generators for Hudsonville Homes and Outbuildings</h2>
    <p>
      A lot of Hudsonville properties are not just a house — they're a house plus a pole barn, a shop, or a detached
      garage on a subpanel. That changes the generator plan. You may want the home fully covered and the outbuilding on
      essential circuits only, or a single larger unit feeding both. We map what actually needs to stay on before sizing
      anything.
    </p>
    <p>
      Rural and semi-rural service here also leans on well pumps, which carry a hard startup load that a too-small
      generator will choke on. If your outbuilding feeders or subpanels need work as part of the project, that's covered
      under <a href="/electrical-repairs-hudsonville-mi">electrical repairs in Hudsonville</a>, and
      <a href="/panel-upgrades-hudsonville-mi">panel upgrades</a> if the main service is at its limit.
    </p>
  </section>
</ServiceCityPage>
